The paper focuses on the chase procedure, which is a fundamental algorithm in database theory and falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the termination and complexity of the chase, which are topics related to logic and complexity theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the connection between the chase and word rewriting, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis and taxonomy of the chase variations also involve concepts from data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
